            . I am an officer. On the 8th of February, about twenty minutes past seven o'clock, I was near the prosecutors', and saw the prisoner and two others walking backwards and forwards by their shop; they then crossed over to me; I secured the prisoner, and found six books in his hat - these are two of them; he said, "Waddington, you know I am a bookbinder - they are all my own;" my partner took the other two, but the bill is thrown out against them.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I am a <rs id="t18270215-182-viclabel978" type="occupation">bookbinder</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270215-182-victim1016 t18270215-182-viclabel978"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270215-182-victim1017 t18270215-182-viclabel978"></join>; there are a thousand of these books - I sell books in the street, and bought these at the corner of Fleet-street.</p>
